{"key":"post-10057521","value":"<?xml version=\"1.0\"?>\n<post>\n<id>10057521</id>\n<content>I use a flowhood, so I simply lift the lid off and pour the water right in from jar to jar, and jar to flask.&amp;nbsp; By the time you guys get into bulk growing where you want that much LC, you really need to pony up the dough for a flowhood.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Mostly, I just use that tek to make syringes for demonstrating the brf tek at schools and such.&amp;nbsp; For my own growing, I do grain inoculations in quart jars from agar wedges, and when those are grown out and tested, I do grain to grain transfers into filter patch bags of rye that hold 6 to 7 quarts.&amp;nbsp; Each of those rye bags will inoculate 20 more, so I can expand mycelium WAY faster that way than by using LC.&amp;nbsp; Syringes are for kids.&lt;br /&gt;RR</content>\n<name>RogerRabbit</name>\n<next>10057568</next>\n<prev>10057491</prev>\n<first>10056857</first>\n<last>10099242</last>\n<when>1238217829</when>\n<utime>03/28/09 08:23 AM</utime>\n</post>"}